The Krug National Park (Kruger National Park, KNP) is located northeast South Africa and winds east along the border with Mozambique, north border, Zimbabwe, and its southern border is represented by the Crocodile River.
With an area of 19,500 km², the park comprises 14 different eco zones, each of which gives life to a different wildlife.
